})\\times10^{-3}$ and $\\mathcal B(\\Lambda^+_c\\rightarrow\n\\Lambda(1405)[\\rightarrow pK^-]e^+\\nu_e)=(0.42\\pm0.19_{\\rm stat.}\\pm0.04_{\\rm\nsyst.})\\times10^{-3}$. Combining these with the inclusive semileptonic\n$\\Lambda_c^+$ branching fraction measured by BESIII, the relative fraction is\ndetermined to be $[\\mathcal{B}(\\Lambda_c^+\\rightarrow\npK^-e^+\\nu_e)/\\mathcal{B}(\\Lambda_c^+\\rightarrow X e^+\\nu_e)]=(2.1\\pm0.4_{\\rm\nstat.}\\pm0.2_{\\rm syst.})\\%$, which provides a clear confirmation that\nsemileptonic $\\Lambda_c^+$ decays are not saturated by the $\\Lambda\n\\ell^+\\nu_{\\ell}$ final state.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 23 Jul 2022 10:18:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 2 Sep 2022 14:16:25 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 28 Dec 2022 02:49:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-02"}
